BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:HJbMFNnVqC-LQG_oW1xeW
SUMMARY:Type Design Basics
DTSTAMP:20260327T024900Z
DTSTART:20260408T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Class Overview\n\nSo you want to design a typeface? Learn how t
	o hand-draw letters and digitize them to create your own unique functional
	 font! In this practical workshop\, students will create an original text 
	typeface based on traditional European calligraphy. Whether you want to de
	velop your typography skills\, improve your lettering practice\, or become
	 a type designer\, learning the fundamentals of type design can bring your
	 skills to the next level.\n\nExplore both analog media \\(pen on paper\\)
	 and digital media \\(computer\\). Learn how to use a calligraphy pen to d
	evelop an understanding of the underlying structure of the Latin alphabet.
	 Then you can work on improving your drawings digitally\, and create a typ
	eface using Glyphs \\(or the font editor of your choice\\).  \n\nClass tim
	e is dedicated to working on your project with individualized feedback\, s
	upplemented by lectures\, technical demonstrations\, and group critique. B
	y the end of the class\, you will have a working text typeface of your own
	 creation\, as well as a sketch-to-screen workflow that you can use for fu
	ture font creation.\n\nStudents will be encouraged to spend up to 10 hours
	 on homework outside of class time. Designing a typeface is a laborious pr
	ocess\, but time flies when experimenting\, drawing\, and editing!\n\nThis
	 class is offered in partnership with the amazing Seattle Creative Academy
	 \\(but this class is not part of their program and is not for credit/degr
	ee\\)! See also: Experimental Lettering and other Graphic Design or art cl
	asses on our website.\n\nLearning Objectives\n\nLearn the basics of callig
	raphy\n\nUnderstand the structure and patterning of the Latin alphabet\n\n
	Create your own original letterforms\n\nDigitize and refine your original 
	design\n\nLearn how to optimize a typeface for text\n\nBecome familiar wit
	h a sketch-to-screen digital type design workflow\n\nWho Might Enjoy This 
	Class?\n\nAnyone who wants to develop their own custom font\n\nGraphic des
	igners\, illustrators\, lettering artists\, type designers -- anyone with 
	related experience who would like to hone their type design skills\n\nArch
	itects\, engineers\, artists\, crafters\, writers\, book lovers -- anyone 
	interested in the form of letters who would enjoy creating and using their
	 own handmade font\n\nNo prerequisites\, but basic graphic design/typograp
	hy knowledge is recommended\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/detai
	ls/type-design-basics/18345520/2026-04-07T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Cul
	ture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/type-design-basics/183455
	20/2026-04-07T00
LOCATION:Seattle Central College Continuing Education\, 1701 Broadway\, Sea
	ttle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
